===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|when|when(ne)|lang=enm}}, {{term|whan|whan(ne)|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|hwenne|lang=ang}}, {{term|hwænne|lang=ang}}, {{term|hwonne||when|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*hwannē||at what time, when}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*kʷo-}}, {{term/t|ine-pro|*kʷi-||interrogative base}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|wanneer||when|lang=nl}} and {{term|wen||when, if|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|wann||when|lang=de}} and {{term|wenn||when, if|lang=de}}, {{etyl|got|-}} {{term|𐍈𐌰𐌽||tr=ƕan|when, how|lang=got|sc=Goth}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|quandō||when|lang=la}}. More at {{l|en|who}}.

Interjection sense: a playful misunderstanding of "say when" (i.e. say when you want me to stop) as "say [the word] ''when''".

